content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #77737 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
Wondering how to approach this issue, the code looks very similar to the mcve in the mentioned issue discussed yesterday 75992 - do we link to the duplicate and close?
if it's duplicate we can de-prioritise it, but i think we shouldn't close the issue
Fair was asking the logistics of it :)

WIth this added attention that the linked issue is getting #75992, this issue links to it and the issue in actix-web actix-web/issues/1688. I was wondering if an issue gets enough attention is there ground to reprioritize ( I realise it is already a P-high so maybe not much to gain in this situation )

DPC said:

if it's duplicate we can de-prioritise it, but i think we shouldn't close the issue

why not if it's a duplicate?

I am undecided on this one. Like suggested, I'd probably unprioritized it until a more concise MCVE is found or (also suggested) this is fairly a duplicate and can follow #75992.
Also closing for me could be fine, I mean if the #75992 will be fixed but the fix does not apply to #77737, the reporter of #77737 can always reopen it, right?
(unrelated, just discovered that on this Zulip stream issues are automatically linked by writing #123456, no need to manually craft the markdown :) )
and you can also use a lot of shortcuts like triagebot#123, forge#123, compiler-team#123 and many more :)

apiraino said:

(unrelated, just discovered that on this Zulip stream issues are automatically linked by writing #123456, no need to manually craft the markdown :) )

You can use those in any stream, not just this one. I think they work in PMs too
it works on this zulip instance because it is configured to match rust-lang/rust as a repo :stuck_out_tongue:
awesome, thanks :thumbs_up:
